{
  "texts": [
    "According to the 3 degree of freedom vertical vibration mechanics model of elevator developed in Fig. 5, assume that all displacements are positive upward and angular displacements are positive counterclockwise.",
    "The dynamic equations of the system are established based on the Lagrange equation:",
    "T-Kinetic energy of the system; U-Potential energy of the system; D-System dissipation factor;",
    "x-Generalized displacement (or angular displacement); ẋ-Generalized velocity (or angular velocity); Q -Generalized force (excitation force or excitation moment).",
    "Mechanical model of vertical vibration in 3 degrees of freedom for 1:1 traction elevator."
  ]
}